question:
In a Jenkins pipeline, what does the following stage do?
stage('Build') {
    steps {
        sh 'mvn clean package -DskipTests'
    }
}

In a Jenkins pipeline integrating Docker, what does the following step do?
stage('Docker Build & Push') {
    steps {
        sh 'docker build -t myrepo/myapp:${BUILD_NUMBER} .'
        sh 'docker push myrepo/myapp:${BUILD_NUMBER}'
    }
}

What does the following Declarative Jenkinsfile section configure?
environment {
    DOCKER_REGISTRY = 'docker.io/myuser'
    IMAGE_TAG = "${env.BUILD_NUMBER}"
}

In a Jenkins pipeline, what does the 'post' block do?
post {
  success { mail to: 'team@company.com', subject: 'Build Passed' }
  failure { slackSend message: 'Build Failed!' }
}

What does the following Jenkins pipeline code demonstrate?
stage('Deploy to Kubernetes') {
    steps {
        withKubeConfig([credentialsId: 'k8s-cred']) {
            sh 'kubectl set image deployment/myapp myapp=myrepo/myapp:${BUILD_NUMBER}'
        }
    }
}
